# Example .env file for LinkedIn Integration
# Copy this to .env and fill in your credentials

# Required: OAuth Credentials
LINKEDIN_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here
LINKEDIN_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret_here
LINKEDIN_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_access_token_here

# Optional: API Configuration
LINKEDIN_API_VERSION=v2
LINKEDIN_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/auth/callback

# =============================================================================
# HOW TO GET THESE VALUES:
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. LINKEDIN_CLIENT_ID & LINKEDIN_CLIENT_SECRET
#    - Go to https://www.linkedin.com/developers/apps
#    - Click "Create app"
#    - Fill in app details (name, page, privacy policy)
#    - Copy Client ID and Client Secret from "Auth" tab
#
# 2. LINKEDIN_ACCESS_TOKEN
#    OPTION A: Use built-in OAuth flow (recommended)
#    - Run: npm run linkedin auth start
#    - Browser opens to LinkedIn authorization
#    - Authorize app
#    - Access token displayed and saved
#
#    OPTION B: Manual OAuth flow
#    - Build authorization URL with Client ID
#    - Authorize and get code
#    - Exchange code for access token
#    - See setup guide for detailed steps
#
# 3. LINKEDIN_API_VERSION (optional)
#    - Current version: v2
#    - LinkedIn uses versioned API endpoints
#
# 4. LINKEDIN_REDIRECT_URI (optional)
#    - Default: http://localhost:3000/auth/callback
#    - Must match URI in LinkedIn app settings
#    - Change if using different port/domain
#
# =============================================================================
# OAUTH SCOPES REQUIRED:
# =============================================================================
#
# ☑️ r_liteprofile - View basic profile information
# ☑️ r_emailaddress - View email address
# ☑️ w_member_social - Share content on your behalf
# ☑️ r_organization_social - View organization posts
# ☑️ w_organization_social - Manage organization posts
#
# Grant these scopes in your LinkedIn app's "Products" tab
#
# =============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# =============================================================================
#
# Run: npm run linkedin setup
#
# For detailed OAuth setup guide, see SETUP.md
#
# =============================================================================
# NOTES:
# =============================================================================
#
# - Access tokens expire after 60 days
# - Refresh tokens not currently supported in this implementation
# - Re-run OAuth flow when token expires
# - LinkedIn heavily restricts API access without Partnership
# - This skill uses features available to all developers
#
# =============================================================================
